If $f(a)=b$ and $f(b)=4$, then what is the value of $a-b$?

chatgpt_solution:
From the graph, we see that the point $(a,b)$ lies on the graph of $y=f(x)$. Therefore, $f(a)=b$. We are given that $f(b)=4$. Since $f$ is invertible, this means that $f^{-1}(4)=b$. Hence, the point $(4,b)$ lies on the graph of $y=f^{-1}(x)$. 

